# {{ project_name }} — frontend (React + TypeScript + Vite)

A Vite single-page app with a typed Axios API client, a feature-based layout, and a Vitest + React
Testing Library suite.

## Run

From the repo root, the easiest path is Docker (no local Node needed):

```bash
docker compose up --build        # starts db + backend + frontend
```

Native local dev (requires Node 22+):

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev                      # http://localhost:5173
```

The app reads the backend URL from `VITE_API_URL` (see `.env.example`); it defaults to
`http://localhost:{{ api_port }}`.

## Test, lint, type-check, build

```bash
npm run test                     # Vitest + Testing Library
npm run lint                     # ESLint (flat config)
npm run typecheck                # tsc --noEmit
npm run build                    # type-check + production bundle
```

## Layout

```
src/
  main.tsx               # entry point
  App.tsx                # shell
  api/client.ts          # shared Axios instance (base URL from env)
  api/items.ts           # typed API calls for the items resource
  types/item.ts          # shared types (mirror the backend schemas)
  features/items/
    useItems.ts          # data hook (state + fetching)
    ItemsPage.tsx        # presentational page
    ItemsPage.test.tsx   # component tests (API mocked)
  test/setup.ts          # jest-dom matchers
```

To add a feature, create `src/features/<name>/`, add a typed API module under `src/api/`, and keep
data logic in a hook. See `.claude/rules/react-patterns.md` for the full recipe.
